A train carrying aluminum products departs from Gongxing station of the Chengdu-Kunming Railway and heads for Hanoi, Vietnam on April 18, 2022. This is the first customized train from Chengdu's airport to Hanoi. So far, Chengdu has operated 52 international trains, transporting more than 2,000 containers with a value of 320 million yuan ($50 million). Photo: cnsphotoThe freight value of China-Vietnam cross-border freight trains has more than doubled since the beginning of this year, customs data showed, revealing a continued robust trade growth between China and Southeast Asia. The Pingxiang Railway Port supervised a total of 202,000 tons of imported and exported goods in the first quarter of this year, an increase of 95.8 percent over the same period last year; the total value is 6.32 billion yuan ($972 million), a year-on-year increase of 240.7 percent. Among them, the growth of imported fruit transportation witnessed a jump, data from Nanning Customs showed. Located on the China-Vietnam border, Pingxiang is China's biggest road fruit import and export port, and the Pingxiang Railway Port is the only border international railway port in South China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.Different cities in China have been busy opening freight trains. On April 15, a freight train loaded with Dell-branded computer parts departed from Chengdu International Railway Port in Southwest China's Sichuan Province, heading for Vietnam.This is the first direct train from a western Chinese city to Vietnam. The whole journey is about 1,841 km, of which about 130 km is outside China. The train will cross China's border via Pingxiang in Guangxi, and is expected to arrive at the destination station in Vietnam seven days later.Since the beginning of this year, to meet demand from manufacturing enterprises, international freight trains from Chengdu shipping goods to Vietnam have shifted from rail-sea combined transportation to solely railway transportation. The journey requires a track-gauge change on the China-Vietnam border."After the launch of the freight train service, the transport time from Chengdu to Vietnam was shortened by two to three days, while avoiding maritime transportation risks, reducing the cost borne by enterprises, and providing support for expanding the Southeast Asian market," said sources with Dell, according to Xinhua News Agency.A freight train carrying 82 TEUs of goods departed from Hefei, East China's Anhui Province, headed for Hanoi, Vietnam, in February.Official data showed that bilateral trade volume between China and Vietnam exceeded $230 billion last year, and China has remained Vietnam's largest trading partner for many years, and Vietnam continues to be China's largest trading partner in ASEAN.Zhao Lijian, spokesperson of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, said on Friday that the newly opened China-Vietnam cross-border freight trains have injected new impetus into bilateral trade, and that China is willing to work with the Vietnamese side to continue to promote the efficiency of cross-border railway intermodal transportation and guarantee the supply chain.The remarks were a response after a spokesperson of Vietnam's foreign ministry said in April that some cross-border freight trains between Vietnam and Chinese localities such as Sichuan and Anhui have been put into operation recently. Vietnam stands ready to work with China to promote the stable, balanced and sustainable development of bilateral trade to deliver real benefits to both countries, said the spokesperson.Customs data also showed that the railroad transport between China and Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) increased significantly by 3.5 times in the first quarter of this year.China's trade with ASEAN totaled 1.35 trillion yuan in the first quarter of 2022, an increase of 8.4 percent year-on-year, as ASEAN comes back as China's largest trading partner after the EU surpassed it in the first two months this year, customs data showed.Global Times